#~ msgid ""
#~ "When using the &turtlelang; programming language you create new things. "
#~ "If you write a program you will often need <link linkend=\"containers"
#~ "\">containers</link> and in some cases you need <link linkend=\"learn"
#~ "\">learn</link> to create new commands. When making a new command with "
#~ "<link linkend=\"learn\">learn</link> you will have to specify a name."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Cando empregue a linguaxe de programación &turtlelang; pode crear novos "
#~ "textos. Se escrebe un programa a miúdo precisará <link linkend="
#~ "\"containers\">contedores</link> e nalgúns casos <link linkend=\"learn"
#~ "\">define</link> para crear novos comandos. Cando faga un novo comando "
#~ "con <link linkend=\"learn\">define</link> terá que especificar un nome."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "You can choose any name, as long as it does not already have a meaning. "
#~ "For instance you cannot name a function <link linkend=\"forward"
#~ "\">forward</link>, since that name is already used for an internal "
#~ "command. <screen>\n"
#~ "# here forward is used as a new command, \n"
#~ "# but it already has a meaning so \n"
#~ "# this will produce an error:\n"
#~ "learn forward {\n"
#~ "  print \"this is invalid\"\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "# this works:\n"
#~ "learn myforward {\n"
#~ "  print \"this is ok\"\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "</screen> Names can contain only letters, numbers and underscores (_). "
#~ "Yet they have to start with a letter. Container names have to start with "
#~ "the container prefix ($)."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Pode escoller calquera nome mentres non teña xa asinado un significado. "
#~ "Por exemplo non pode crear unha función chamada <link linkend=\"forward"
#~ "\">avanza</link>, porque este nome xa é empregado por un comando interno. "
#~ "<screen>\n"
#~ "# aquí emprégase avanza como un comando novo,\n"
#~ "# pero xa ten un significado, polo que \n"
#~ "# dará un erro:\n"
#~ "define avanza {\n"
#~ "  escrebe \"isto non é válido\"\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "\n"
#~ "# isto funciona:\n"
#~ "define adianta {\n"
#~ "  escrebe \"isto serve\"\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ "</screen> Os nomes só poden conter letras, número e trazos baixos (_), e "
#~ "teñen que comezar por unha letra. Os nomes de contedor teñen que comezar "
#~ "co prefixo de contedor ($)."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "# here forward is used as a container, \n"
#~ "# starting with the $ prefix, so it does\n"
#~ "# not conflict with the forward command\n"
#~ "$forward = 20\n"
#~ "print $forward"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "# aquí emprégase avanza como un contedor,\n"
#~ "# polo que se prefixa cun $, polo que non\n"
#~ "# entra en conflito co comando avanza\n"
#~ "$avanza = 20\n"
#~ "escrebe $avanza"

